Jalingo, April 17, 2021 (NAN) A police orderly attached to Mr Shoban Tikari, Chairman of Takum local government council of Taraba, was on Saturday killed by suspected bandits who opened fire on the chairman’s vehicle in Dogo-Gawa village in Takum LGA.  The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the deceased policeman was of the 67 Mobile Police Squadron, located in the area. Tikari, who confirmed the attack, said the militia, in their numbers, launched an attack on his motorcade while on his way to Takum, claiming the life of the deceased in the process. The chairman, who declined giving the name of the deceased, called on the Federal government to deploy more security personnel to the area. Takum and Wukari councils, in southern Taraba have in recent times witnessed a surge of bandit attacks leading to death of civilians and security personnel.  (NAN) Suspected bandits have set a Catholic priest at Kufai Amadu in Takum Local Government Area of Taraba State on fire. This comes barely 24 hours after gunmen raided villages in the state killing two people. Reverend Father David Tanko was ambushed while he was heading to Takum for a peace… In "News" The Miyetti Allah Cattle Breeders Association of Nigeria (MACBAN) on Sunday condemned the arrest of its members by the police and the Takum Council Chairman, Shiban Tikari. North-East zonal chairman of the association, Alhaji Mafindi Danburam, stated this at a press conference in Jalingo. According to him, some Miyetti Allah… In "News" Taraba - The photo of the young Catholic priest who was killed and set ablaze by armed bandits has been revealed.   Yesterday, 29th August, the sad news emeregd that a Catholic Priest, Rev. Father David Tanko at Kufai Amadu in Takum local government area of Taraba state. Now a photo of the… In "News"